value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of any of the layers that make up the thin layer of neural tissue lining the back of the eyeball which contains visual receptors.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the layer of light-sensitive receptors in the eye.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the photoreceptor layer which contains stacks of membranous discs that are rich in the visual pigment rhodopsin.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the photoreceptor layer which contains the machinery of the cell (mitochondria, golgi, endoplasmic reticulum, etc).

label.value: retinal outer nuclear layer morphology trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the retinal layer that contains the nuclei and cell bodies of rods and cones.

label.value: retinal outer plexiform layer morphology trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the retinal layer that is the site of synapses between the rods and cones (axons) and the horizontal and bipolar cells (dendrites).

label.value: retinal inner nuclear layer morphology trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the retinal layer which contains the cell bodies of bipolar, horizontal, and amacrine cells.

label.value: retinal inner plexiform layer morphology trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the retinal cell layer where bipolar and amacrine cell axons synapse with ganglion cell dendrites.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the nonvascular, resilient, flexible connective tissue of the external portion of the organ of hearing.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of any of the small bones of the middle ear.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the region of the body that includes the front part of the head from the chin to the top of the forehead, where the mouth, eyes, nose, and other features are located.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the oral cavities of the face.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the mucus-secreting tissue that lines the oral cavity.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical form or contours of the oral cavity.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the roof of the mouth in vertebrates formed anteriorly by a bony projection of the upper jaw (hard palate) and posteriorly by the fold of connective tissue (soft palate).

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the anterior part of the palate that is supported by and includes the palatal extensions of the maxillary and palatine bones.
The distance from side to side of the roof of the oral cavity.
The distance from point to point along the longest axis of the roof of the oral cavity.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the organs associated with the body's defense against foreign organisms or substances and aberrant native cells.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the primary lymphoid organ that is required for maturation of T cells.
The average distance of the deepest point in the midline of the palate relative to the midline point on the anterior crest of the alveolar gum pad ridge.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the fleshy margins of the mouth.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical form or contours of the fleshy margins of the mouth.
The distance from side to side of the line between the lip and the facial skin around the mouth.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the smaller, largely mucus-secreting, exocrine glands of the oral cavity, consisting of the labial, buccal, molar, lingual, and palatine glands.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the three largest glands of the oral cavity that secrete most of the saliva, including the parotid, submandibular, and sublingual glands.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of either of the large major salivary glands situated beneath the mandible.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the start of the induction and/or formation of any of the paired, metamerically arranged cell masses formed in the embryonic paraxial mesoderm.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the outer layers of solid, hard bone that cover spongy bone; consist of parallel osteons containing mineral deposits and interstitial lamellae.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the deposition or aggregation of coloring matter in the sebaceous gland located behind the eyeball in some species that excretes fluid that facilitates movement of the nictitating membrane.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the directed and orderly movement of macrophages from point to point.
The proportion or number of fingers or toes, or their corresponding parts in other vertebrates.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the chemical reactions and pathways involving a nucleotide, a nucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the glycose moiety; may be mono-, di- or triphosphate; this definition includes cyclic nucleotides (nucleoside cyclic phosphates).
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the free portion of the hair, consisting of the cuticle, cortex, and the medulla.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the outermost layer of the hair shaft.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the principal structural component of the hair shaft.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the central axis of the hair shaft.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the compound gland suspended from the base of the hypothalamus, which secretes somatotropins, prolactin, TSH (thyroid-stimulating hormone), gonadotropins, and adrenal corticotropin.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the pouch of ectoderm that grows out from the upper surface of the embryonic stomodeum and gives rise to the anterior and intermediate lobes of the pituitary gland.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the muscles of the organ of vision during their formation and differentiation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the supporting cells that form the inner and outer walls of the tunnel in the organ of Corti.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the transient embryonic tubes that empty into the cloaca and in the female develop into the oviducts, uterus, and vagina.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the transient embryonic tubes that empty into the cloaca and differentiate into the vas deferens in the male in higher vertebrates.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the male reproductive glands where sperm production occurs.
The proportion or number of unfused, spindle-shaped cells in skeletal muscle that play a role in muscle repair and regeneration.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the cells responsible for epinephrine and norepinephrine secretion.
Any measurable characteristic related to the controlled release of milk from the mammary gland.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the articulation between the parietal bones and the frontal bone.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the articulation between the parietal bones and the occipital bone.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the articulation of the frontal bone from the sagittal suture to the root of the nose.
